The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                                 2                                                                                        NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	Panaji, March 16 (PTI): An alleged Israeli drug peddler in Goa police custody has blamed his jilted Swiss girlfriend for his arrest. Yaniv Benaim alias Atala was caught on spy camera saying police officers were stealing drugs from court lockers.          An officer said Atala had confessed that his girlfriend shot the video and uploaded it on a popular website in 2008. He now says whatever he confessed on video was false. The video was exposed recently by a news channel.                  
	Washington (PTI): An American study has claimed that Indian spices and vermilion contain lead and are harmful to children. About 25 per cent of Indian spices in the US like cardamom, fenugreek, chilli powder have one microgram of lead per gram of product, the study said.                  
	Aligarh (PTI): Researchers at the Aligarh Muslim University claim to have developed a waste disposal system that converts effluents into solid building material, thus reducing environmental damage caused by industrial discharge, in a paper published in the recent Indian Geotechnical Journal.                   
	 Dehra Dun (PTI): A district court has sentenced a man to seven years imprisonment for raping a 15-year-old girl at Sahaspur in Uttarakhand. Jaheer Hasan was held guilty of raping the Class VI student on October 26, 2007. A fine of Rs 5,000 has been imposed on him.                   
	Vadodara (PTI): A woman held with narcotics worth Rs 8.73lakh has been remanded in five days custody, while police are searching for her husband. Police seized 84 gm of brown sugar and Rs 25,050 after a raid on their house in Panigae, Gujarat.                   
	 Srinagar (PTI): A militant has been arrested in Srinagar and a hideout busted in Pulwama in Jammu and Kashmir, sources said onTuesday. A pistol, a magazine and seven cartridges have been recovered.
                                                                                                                                              
